And now, for the stark reality of these convoluted arrangements: a detailed, if somewhat exhausting, catalogue of councils currently operating under the charming umbrella of 'no overall control.' These tables serve as a testament to the persistent fragmentation of local power, illustrating precisely where the electorate has decided that no single faction deserves an unfettered hand. Pay close attention, if you must, to the intricate dance of coalitions and minority administrations – each entry a tiny saga of political compromise, or stubborn refusal to cooperate, playing out in your local area. It’s a lot to take in, I know, but such is the price of wanting details.

